      • setRepositoryLocations

        public void setRepositoryLocations(java.lang.String... repositoryLocations)
        Set additional repository locations for looking repositories that need to be initialized for the application. By default application package is used to look for repositories which makes this not mandatory. However if repositories are out of application package then the packages need to be provided via this method.
        Parameters:
        repositoryLocations - String array of additional repository package locations.
        Since:
        1.0.2

        Returns:
        true if auto inject repositories is enabled; false otherwise.
        Since:
        1.1.0

      • setEnableAutoInject

        public void setEnableAutoInject(boolean enableAutoInject)
        Set annotation based inject repositories enabled. Automatic annotation based repository injection will only become effective on objects that calls DatabaseManager.lookupRepositories(Object) method somewhere in application execution context before the repositories is being used.
        Parameters:
        enableAutoInject - boolean value to define whether annotation based repository injection is enabled.
        Since:
        1.1.0
